section.para:
datarate calculating quickly Since all modes give you the continuum IFs, you start off with one of two base data rates, per cycle. For the 1 MHz modes, the base data rate is:
\mathrm{b}_{\mathrm{cycle}}(1\mathrm{\,MHz}) = 1.573632 \times 10^{6}
bytes per IF. For the 64 MHz modes, the base data rate is:
\mathrm{b}_{\mathrm{cycle}}(64\mathrm{\,MHz}) = 2.5344 \times 10^{4}
bytes per IF.
